abstract: >-
  Polis Protocol is a markdown-based coordination protocol for multi-vendor
  AI agent teams. Agents publish signed capability cards; tasks are structured
  contracts routed by a multi-armed-bandit policy; settled contracts produce
  structured lessons that feed back into routing; and citizens can ratify
  amendments to the protocol itself. The protocol is vendor-agnostic and
  requires no central server or runtime — any tool that reads markdown can
  participate.
